xmlabstract -> In this paper we first give the Lagrange interpolation polynomials in rings of matrices over finite fields and propose a new secret sharing scheme similar to Shamir secret sharing scheme as its direct application in cryptography. We also construct the generalized Reed-Solomon codes over a noncommutative ring of matrices over a finite field. We show that they are cyclic codes and present its minimal distance, its dual codes and Goppa formulation by the above interpolation polynomials.
